  "title": "Explorify",
  "description": "A simplistic, vanilla-friendly collection of new structures.",
  "body": "<a href=\"https://everloste.github.io\"><img alt=\"Button to visit the creator's website\" height=\"48\" src=\"https://everloste.github.io/badges/website-badge.svg\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://everloste.github.io/bluesky\"><img alt=\"Button to visit the creator's Bluesky\" height=\"48\" src=\"https://everloste.github.io/badges/bluesky-badge.svg\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://everloste.github.io/discord\"><img alt=\"Button to join the creator's Discord\" height=\"48\" src=\"https://everloste.github.io/badges/discord-badge.svg\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://everloste.github.io/ko-fi\"><img alt=\"Button to visit the creator's Ko-fi\" height=\"48\" src=\"https://everloste.github.io/badges/ko-fi-badge.svg\"></a>\n\n### ⛺ About\n**Explorify** is a datapack that adds new structures to explore in your Minecraft world!  \n\nThe structures don't only look fairly good (...as good as I can make them :p) but also hopefully fit the game thematically and structurally. They're not meant to be just some random houses, but new things that feel interesting yet familiar.  \n\nI hope you like them!\n\n### 📦 Content\nFor a list of structures see the gallery! I try to keep it up to date.\n\n### 📝 Notes\nFabric mod version requires **[Fabric API](https://modrinth.com/mod/fabric-api)**!\n\nIf you want a config, install **[Cristel Lib](https://modrinth.com/mod/cristel-lib)**. The mod is otherwise configurable using a datapack.\n\nThis mod is still in development and new versions may differ. I may make any changes, including the removal of structures. While Minecraft can handle this and updating the mod will not corrupt your world, it's still best to make backups.  ",
